{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"58926b0f-bfb8-41dc-ba69-8d71722f37e7","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing code, here's exactly what you need to do:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the namespace for your ViewModel and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is **`x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"`** — this tells the XAML compiler the type of the binding context, so every `{Binding ...}` is resolved at compile time instead of at runtime via reflection.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already produce **build errors** for typos or type mismatches. To make this even stricter, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat XAML warnings (including binding issues) as errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for binding path issues. With `x:DataType` set, referencing a nonexistent property (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) will now **fail the build**.\n\n### Quick summary\n\n| What | How |\n|---|---|\n| Enable compiled bindings | Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element |\n| Scope to a sub-element | Put `x:DataType` on any element to change the type for its subtree |\n| Opt out locally | Use `x:DataType=\"\"` on an element to fall back to reflection bindings |\n| Catch errors at build time | Happens automatically — mismatched property names/types become compiler errors |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"18e49f28-c01b-4b32-8efd-348cca3d0c25","outputTokens":717,"requestId":"3C26:16C73:D3552B:1071D9C:6A012901"},"id":"e3657394-5d6d-4546-afcc-eb2ae41a210f","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:55:44.026Z","parentId":"403924f9-9482-405a-ac8d-16a5ba7e9ce1"}
